I did. But I don't think I understand exactly what is going on.
The cards have different powers and icons on them.
You'll see that each power relates to an icon
So Atomic Theory for example, it's powers rely on lightbulbs
If I used that power, I had 5 lightbulbs to my opponents 4, so I would be the only person to use that power
But if I'd used Metric System, that relys on crowns, which my opponent had more of. In that situation, my opponent would get to use that power before I could
That's the basic mechanic of the game.
Some cards will allow you to score points, for every 5 points, you can achieve a level. But to acheive a level, you must have a card in play of that number
